## 5. Data Quality Dimensions
      5.1 Accuracy
        Some negative profit values found
        Discount values exceed expected business rules in some cases
      5.2 Completeness
        Missing customer IDs in ~2.1% records
        Missing product category in some product entries
      5.3 Consistency
        Inconsistent region naming (e.g., "NY", "New York")
        Date formats inconsistent in raw dataset
      5.4 Uniqueness
        Duplicate order IDs detected (1.8%)
      5.5 Validity
        Negative quantity values found in few records
        Invalid discount percentages (>100%) present
      5.6 Timeliness
        Data updated monthly, not real-time

---

## 6. Key Data Issues Identified
Issue Type	                Description	                  Severity

Duplicates	                Duplicate Order IDs	          High
Missing Values	            Customer ID missing	          Medium
Invalid Values	            Negative quantity	            High
Format Issue	              Inconsistent dates	          Medium
Standardization	            Region names inconsistent	    Low

---

## 7. Root Cause Analysis
  Manual data entry errors in sales system
  Lack of validation rules at data entry level
  Multiple data sources not standardized
  Missing data governance policies

---

## 8. Business Impact
  Incorrect revenue calculations
  Misleading product performance insights
  Inaccurate KPI reporting
  Poor decision-making due to unreliable data

---

## 9. Data Cleaning Actions Taken
Issue	                          Action Taken
Duplicates	                    Removed using Order ID deduplication
Missing Values	                Imputed or marked as "Unknown"
Invalid Quantities	            Filtered or corrected using business rules
Region Names	                  Standardized using mapping table
Dates	                          Converted to uniform format

